The paper discusses techniques for solving multi-output regression tasks, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield of "multi-output learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of different base models and loss functions, which are important topics in the broader field of "artificial intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper's focus on applications and the use of Monte Carlo methods suggest that it may also be relevant to the subfields of "computer vision" (cs.CV) and "social and information networks" (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's discussion of different types of data and the need for flexibility suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of "data structures and algorithms" (cs.DS).
